'''Friederike Roth''' (born 6 April 1948) is a [[Germany|German]] writer. She is especially active as a [[playwright]].

Roth was born in [[Sindelfingen]]. She won the [[Johann-Friedrich-von-Cotta-Literatur- und Übersetzerpreis der Landeshauptstadt Stuttgart|City of Stuttgart Literary Prize in 1982]] and the [[Ingeborg Bachmann Prize]] in 1983.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bachmannpreis.eu/en/information/470|title=The Ingeborg Bachmann Prize|publisher=ORF.at|accessdate=13 February 2011}}</ref>

